\log(\frac{1}{2})
\log(2)
 \int_1^\infty \frac{1}{x(x+1)}dx 
 \log(x) - \log(x+1) = \log\left(\frac{x}{x + 1}\right) \Big|_1^\infty 
 \lim_{t\to\infty}\log\left(\frac{x}{x+1}\right)\Big|_1^t 
0-\log(1/2) = -\log(1/2) = \log[(1/2)^{(-1)}] =  \log(2)
-\log(1/2)
\log(1/2)
-\log(1/2) = \log(2)
\lim_{t\rightarrow\infty} \log\left(\frac{x}{x+1}\right)\Big|_1^t  \\=\lim_{t\rightarrow\infty}\log\left(\frac{t}{t+1}\right) - \log\left(\frac{1}{2}\right) \\ =\log(1) - \log\left(\frac{1}{2}\right) = 0 - (-\log(2)) = \log(2)
